                            <comment id="17199426" author="michaelboyles" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2020 14:49:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The only thing which can throw NPE on that line is &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/blob/b0325d4b7142832696d22fea1ea654348a69c675/surefire-providers/surefire-junit47/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/surefire/junitcore/JUnitCoreProvider.java#L294&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this instance of RunOrderCalculator&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/blob/b0325d4b7142832696d22fea1ea654348a69c675/surefire-api/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/surefire/booter/BaseProviderFactory.java#L113&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;only implementation&lt;/a&gt; of the provider, and the return is indeed nullable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This null check seems spurious. It checks directoryScannerParameters, but doesn&apos;t use it for anything. Seems like it should be checking runOrderParameters. When it was &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/blob/877873b08a8fb62c7d31a0019eb2a1b419a2876e/surefire-api/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/surefire/booter/BaseProviderFactory.java#L80&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;originally introduced,&lt;/a&gt; this check made sense, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/commit/13e6736b8cabc04be9b98c71a2a9695391d1f1a1#diff-868fd02a40a6474205d7b259d320b806L86&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;a subsequent change to support parallelizing tests&lt;/a&gt; seemed to break it.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;As a workaround, the reason directoryScannerParameters is null stems from the fact that &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/blob/master/maven-surefire-common/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/plugin/surefire/AbstractSurefireMojo.java#L1832&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;you are using suiteXmlFiles&lt;/a&gt;, so maybe you can find an alternative way to configure your tests, while avoiding using that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17199438" author="jleech92" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2020 14:59:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks very much for the quick and well definitive answer, will look to work around it like you say&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17199453" author="michaelboyles" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2020 15:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to submit a PR to fix that, but it seems like another reason you&apos;re seeing this issue is that you&apos;re mixing Junit and TestNG. Are you expecting that?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you run Maven with debug logging (-X) you should see some line beginning with &quot;Using the provider &amp;lt;some class&amp;gt;&quot;. All the above code I contained within a JUnit provider, but I can see from your profile that you&apos;re including TestNG too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17200461" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2020 01:39:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=maven-surefire.git;a=commit;h=aef6573be8a31f8235786517405b49a6c1ef89c5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=maven-surefire.git;a=commit;h=aef6573be8a31f8235786517405b49a6c1ef89c5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
